Commissioner Erasmus Makodza, accused of corruptly concealing a transaction from a principal, was today freed on $10 000 bail when he appeared at the Harare Magistratesâ€™ Court. Harare regional magistrate Mr Stanley Mambanje also ordered him to report once a month and not interfere with witnesses. He remanded him to March 2. Mrs Netsai Mushayabasa appeared for the State while lawyer Mr Tapiwa Makanza represented Makodza.